snippet: The last round of negotiations with the United States and five other world powers ended in January without progress.
abstract: Iran proposes new round of talks about its nuclear program with the United States along with Russia, China, Britain, France and Germany; announcement comes one month after the West imposed new sanctions over Tehran's uranium enrichment program.
lead_paragraph: The last round of negotiations with the United States and five other world powers ended in January without progress.

headline.main: Iran Asks to Resume Talks on Its Nuclear Program
headline.print_headline: Iran Asks to Resume Talks on Its Nuclear Program
